This paper focuses on the psychological and practical factors that might impact respondents' preferences for autonomous cars' operation. It also discusses the importance of framing and communication in any autonomous car-related debate. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories, including human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cybernetics (cs.CYBER), social and information networks (cs.SI), and robotics (cs.RO).
